review_blob: Cooper color with medium head. Nice smooth body with yeast and raisin aroma. Flavor of dough, brown sugar and malt.
Black with nice carbonation and tan head. Molasses dark chocolate and bread. Clean finish.
Poured hard and drank quick. Nice billowing head with burnt coffee cream and malt taste. Nice finish.
beer_name: Left Hand Hard Wired Nitro Coffee Porter

review_blob: Nice Amber body with tab head. Aroma of barn yard and taste of bitter cranberry, malt and a hint of sweetness.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Nice stout with a tan head that slowly resides. Toasty hops and malt with aromas of spice. Easy drinking and clean finish.
Nice hay color with white topper. Aroma of citrus and malt. Taste of barnyard with orange peel. Nice carbonation and short alcohol aroma at end.
Picked up a pint of the newly launched 902 Brewing Co. Large tan head onto a brown sparkling body. Malt aroma and coffee with a little yeast and alcohol taste. Not enough hop profile for this IPA.

Liter @ pilsner hause in a stein with a Hazy yellow beer. Medium white long lasting head. Aroma of bananas and a bit of cloves in the flavor. But also a malty taste with hints of hops to finish. This is a nice weissbier.
Can into glass releases crisp dark body under nice foam head. Aroma of coffee roasting. Taste of malt, coffee, resin and nice hop notes. This is one of the better cross over IPAs.
Can. Pale yellow with some haze. Watermelon aroma and flavor. A little sweet with a touch of malt character. Interesting beer but not sure wheat and watermelon should coexist.
beer_name: 21st Amendment Hell or High Watermelon Wheat

review_blob: Bottle pours a minimal tan head on a nice amber body without any lacing. Smells of malt and yeast. Taste of a water soaked banana bread. Very thin body.
Blood from a steel can. Nice amber sunset brown body with medium tan head. Aroma of yeast and alcohol. Flavor of bread, malts, cherry and perfect amount of carbonation. Nice crisp finish.
Large white head from a cloudy golden body. Straw aroma filled with slight cranberry and a touch of orange to cut the bitters. Very drinkable ale.
Bottle pours dark maroon with thin tan head. Looks and smells like cherry coke. Taste of port with spice and malt. Nice even balance with quick finish.
Bottle hazy blonde ale with medium white head. Smell of citrus, straw and taste of lemon, coriander and a bit of orange zest. Even body and a little flat rate profile.
Dark body small tan head. Malt chocolate aroma and tobacco, nut, licorice taste. Nicely carbonated and drinkable.

Bottle and then amber foggy ale with medium tan head. Aroma of week old brown banana, rising bread and a hint of cover. Taste of gum, orange bringing some sweetness and malt finish. Nice bubbly and short sweet finish.

Thin tan head on top of brown turning black body. Aroma a smidge alcoholic and a bit like wood lacquer. Super smooth palate with chocolate, malt, and coffee notes. Nice finish with sweetness ending at satisfaction.

Huge head per bottle conditioning with a nice translucent brown body. Some major notes with grassy tones. I would cellar this to bring out the brett as the farmyard does not represent enough to make this a real upside brown.

Rich dark body with tan head. Aroma of raspberries and some coffee essence. Taste of dark chocolate, bitter and coffee grinds. On the other spectrum is the tart raspberries. Interesting but not well balanced.
Nice cascading head fills a ruby colored basin. Faint sweet hop smell and taste of toffee with burnt tobacco finish. A little flat but enjoyable.
Love the quart bottle and the golden beer that followed. Aroma of bread yeast and spice. Taste of bitter hop melded with malt for a cereal everspice with hint of liquorice. Medium length finish.
Robust black body with tab head was a cool fusion of black lager with kolsch finish. Rich but drinkable malt with nice spice finish.
Proud to drink a can of one of Americas oldest brews. Classic water corn grass flavor but just enough hop flavor to make it enjoyable.
Can on a hot day. Not a lot of aroma and water downed Kolsch with some slight grassy notes. No hop flavor short finish.
White on tan with water body and clean finish. Lemon flavor with a little yeast aroma.
The bloom abounds over a foggy haze of wheat fields with apricot and lemon in the distance.

From the can in my hand on the beach and enjoying a very crisp hop aroma. Flavor is hoppy but not overly bitter with a bit of citrus and a touch of malt. Very very clean palate and nice short finish without the classic over hopped residue lingering.

Amazing how fast the thin head dissipates. Smells of alcohol and floral arrangements. Taste a little bitter and some pomegranates slash rhubarb. Palette is on the thin side with a nice extended finish.
Straw golden color with a sharp dry flavor and a little bitter ending. Aroma of hay and a taste of slight skunk.
Bottle brown and nice lacing and sedimentation. Yeast and bread aroma with dry raisin and flat malt flavor. Nice sweet finish.
Khaki top with brown underneath. Yeast bread aroma with anise malt flavor. Slight sweet finish.
Large head with bubbling brown body. Higher carbonation level than most brownies. This better has a slightly astringent flavor which may be from the choice of a singular hop, the Citra.
This beer is aptly named as the sun isnt shining through this muddled ale. Wheat with over ripe lemon and short finish.
Cooper red firing up the kiln producing clouds of tan head. Sweet aroma malt flavor with tart hop finish. Interesting and different.

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob: Massive cloud of foam released from the inferno. Massive amount of carbonation packed into this devils brew. Straw and wheat champagne with hidden alcohol behind the lacing.
Bottle into pint glass. Hoppy floral with minimal pine and on the bitter side. A touch of sweetness at the end but it quickly retreats.
Nitro bottle had nice cooper color with quickly evaporating tan head. Malt flavor with hops in the background. Taste is well rounded and easy drinking ale.
Nitro tap delivers a lively dark ale with small white head. Chocolate aroma with a sweet malt caramel cocoa mix. Tiny carbonation bubbles and nice sweet short finish deliver this carton to the door.
Nice amber hue and golden head for this well crafted brew. Oats, granola notes with a nice hop balance. Finishes on the floral side.

Bottle Batch 12 Oct 2013. Small tan head on dark brown with a Burgundy glowing body. Elderflower aroma lingers and flavors of chocolate, brown sugar and a light and sweet coffee. Alcohol finish but it is very slight.
Draught with thin head on dark brown body. Aroma of roasted coffee and hint of licorice. Taste a little bitter and has a slick consistency.
Sparkling clear body with maximum golden head. Aroma of elderflower and nice hoppy flavor with a champagne palate.
Golden with sizeable white head. Nice even toned hops and the double fermentation added a malt with slight spice condition.
Small tan head on a vibrant burnt orange body. Has a real musty smell. Sweet sugary nutmeg to start and a slight malty pumpkin finish.
Perfect pairing of imperial stout and pumpkin. The stout flattens or the spicy pumpkin flavor to make a great drinking beer for any harvest moon.
Golden ale with white head. A nice hop balance ties the high alcohol content with a underlying pilsner makes.
Hazy IPA with hops but rounded out as a session. Bitter with hints of floral and pine. The finish is a lingering yeasty flavor.
Great ruby color and medium white head. A slight aroma of grape but only slight sweetness. Harkens back to 60.
A pleasant pink copper body below a trash head. A not to sweet raspberry ale with mild hop notes. Body a little thin and nice tart finish.
